.jumbotron
  .text-center
    %h1 Who agree?
    %h5 World wide database of who agree on yes/no questions and controversial statements
    %br
    - if current_user
      = link_to "New question", "/statement", class: "btn btn-primary"
    - else
      = link_to image_tag("twitter-login.png"), "/auth/twitter"

%section#info
  .container
    .col-md-4
      %h3 1. Ask a yes/no question
    .col-md-4
      %h3 2. Share it on Twitter
    .col-md-4
      %h3 3. People gather who agree

#statements
  .container
    .row
      - 3.times do |i|
        = render partial: "row", locals: { statement: @statements[i], individual: @individuals[i] }
    .row
      - 3.times do |i|
        = render partial: "row", locals: { statement: @statements[i + 3], individual: @individuals[i + 3] }
    .row
      - 3.times do |i|
        = render partial: "row", locals: { statement: @statements[i + 6], individual: @individuals[i + 6] }

.jumbotron
  .text-center
    %h1 Not just quotes
    %h3
      If Barack Obama says that climate change is a threat, we can add him to the list of people who agree that climate change is real.
      %br
      %br
      = image_tag "climate-change.jpg"
.jumbotron
  .text-center
    %h1 Liquid Democracy
    %h5 Mix of direct and representative democracy
    %br
    = image_tag("people.gif")

%section#liquid_democracy_info
  .container
    .col-md-4
      %h3 1. When you elect an online representative, you vote whatever s/he votes.
    .col-md-4
      %h3 2. But if you vote on concrete issues, your vote counts instead.
    .col-md-4
      %h3 3. Change your representative/s at any time.


